parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump does not prime properly
the vehicle experiences difficulty starting or running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel filler neck or tube can cause fuel leaks, leading to safety risks, fire hazards, and environmental damage.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel filler neck or tube
the fuel filler neck or tube is damaged or corroded
the fuel cap is difficult to remove or replace.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty or incorrect
the fuel gauge is stuck on a specific reading
the fuel gauge does not respond to changes in fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake light malfunction can cause confusion and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake light comes on while driving
even after the initial problem has been fixed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the vehicle to wander on the road, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle wanders on the road
the power steering pump has a broken steel shaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The over-center torque adjustment on steering can cause the vehicle to wander on the road, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle wanders on the road
the steering system requires over-center torque adjustment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling on downhill descents can cause a loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine quits or stalls when driving downhill at approximately 55 miles per hour
loss of power
inability to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent illumination of the check engine light can indicate a underlying problem with the vehicle's engine or emissions system, which if left unchecked, can lead to decreased fuel efficiency, reduced performance, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on and off
the light may flash or stay steady
the vehicle may experience a loss of power or hesitation
the vehicle may produce excessive emissions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuse Failure Causing Running Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of fuses can cause the running lights to malfunction, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Running lights do not turn on
running lights flicker or dim
fuses blow repeatedly
modified components fail to resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Causing Running Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the running lights to malfunction, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Running lights do not turn on
running lights flicker or dim
fuses blow repeatedly
modified components fail to resolve the issue.
